The paper focuses on the application of explainable AI to face recognition and biometrics, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the societal implications of these technologies, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper presents case studies that involve machine learning algorithms, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
